{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, countries like the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Angola, and the Central African Republic score lower, influenced by challenges in infrastructure and governance.",
    "AI discussions in Africa revolve around public sector reform, education, research, national competitiveness, and tech partnerships.",
    "Countries with adequate capacities focus on skill and capacity development.",
    "For instance, Kenya has integrated coding into its national curriculum, and South Africa hosts events like the Deep Learning Indaba conference to bolster local AI capacities.",
    "In Nigeria, the National Centre for AI and Robotics (NCAIR) promotes research and development in AI and related technologies."
  ]
}